article.headline: Holy Cross defeats Loyola (MD) 86-78
article.description: — Will Batchelder scored 18 points as Holy Cross beat Loyola (MD) 86-78 on Saturday.
article.story: WORCESTER, Mass. -- — Will Batchelder scored 18 points as Holy Cross beat Loyola (MD) 86-78 on Saturday. Batchelder shot 5 for 8 (2 for 4 from 3-point range) and 6 of 6 from the free throw line for the Crusaders (5-14, 2-4 Patriot League). Caleb Kenney added 17 points while shooting 7 of 10 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line, and they also had seven rebounds. Bo Montgomery and Joe Octave both had 14 points. Deon Perry led the Greyhounds (3-16, 1-5) in scoring, finishing with 26 points and four assists. Loyola (MD) also got 16 points and 11 rebounds from Alonso Faure. D'Angelo Stines also recorded 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
